{"/service/ndnp/vnstcsc/batch_vnstcsc_duggan_ver01/data/sn84037526/00513681343/1958031801/0255.xml":{"full_text":"The Bt. Croix Avis\n<cHAMPION OF PUBLIC RIGHT AND JUSTICE\"\nPrinted publishedbveryaftemoon except Sundays holidays by\nBRODHURST'S PRINTERY\nChristi ansted\u2018 ted, St.:CrOix. U. S. Virgin Islands\nTelephone 48 P. O. Box 333\nEditer Manages Canute A. Brodhurst\nF oo Circulation Anna \ufb01rodhurst\nal Subscription Rno?n. L\nSc pur copy SI.OO per month sl2. per year. All subscriptions are\npaayable in advance.\nEntered as Second Class matter May 26, 1917 at the Post Office at\nChristianstsed, St. Croix, V. I, under the Act of March 9, .1897\nVOL. 114\nEditorial T R e\nGt RECESSION' WITH. US\nBOTH POLITICAL parties on the mainland are!\nworking frantically to come up with the most spectacu\nlar and eye-catching sclution to the current recession\nwhich is plaguing the nation. This is an election year,\nand no side wants to be caught napping at the switch.\nEverybody is therefore trying to do those things which!\nwill win for itself the greatest possible credit. This is{\nonly natural, and possibly the only way it can be played|\nunder the present political system, il\nTHAT THERE IS a recession, even the Republicans\nconcede, for with over five million men unemployed\nthere is no denying the fact that something is wrong\u00e9\nwith the economy. But taking it further, the Democrats\ncontend that things are serious, and that somethings\nshould be done' right-away. The Republicans, on the\nother hand, while admitting that all is not right,\u2018never-:\ntheless contend that the situation is not serious enough\nto warrant action at this time. They say that a little\nmore time and things will right themselves.\nTHE PICTURE IS not a pretty one. Each month\nthe number of unemployed increases. Many sections of\nthe nation are hard hit, especially in the heavily popu\nlated industrial areas. Cause for this is the cutback in\nproduction of automobiles and machinery, machine\u2019\ntools and airplanes. i\nSENATOR LYNDON JOHNSON of Texas has come\nup with a resolution calling for a speed-up of public\nwerks expenditures as away out. Jobs would be provid\ned for at least half a million, and more would follow.\nSenator Johnson also has another resolution to present\nwhich would call for military public Works. s\nALL SIDES AGREE that something must be done.\nThe Democrats are concerned lest the time slips by. At;\nany rate it is good to know that attention is being given\nto the problem before things get completely out of hand.\n\nTUESDAY, MARCH: 18, 1958\nTHE ST. CROIX AVIS\nFas\u00ae\nT\u2019 \ufb01\u2018\nTt eR T\ne\nTWO FLIGHTS WEEKLY TO\n|E VIA SAN JUAN\n-ON GIANT RADAR-EQUIPPED\nF 'SUPER-6 CLIPPERS*\nB\ni 3\nK *113.00 ROUND TRIP TOURIST FARE\n1 SEE YOUR TRAVEL AGENT OR y\n4\n1 PAN\u2014\n\nWORLD'S MOST EXPERIENCED AIRLINE,\nE.S. Crawford,\nGeneral Traffic Sales Agents\nChristiansted, Frederiksted, Stl. Croix, V.I.\nSTX=S74-MIA R Tt s e\nT o Byl\nSTRENGTH\nR =TS\n\no UmTY\nNO. 61\nCard of Thanks\nWe take this opportunity to\n\u2018express-our deepest thanks to'\nthe many friends and well\nwishers who sent tokens or ex-!\npressed sympathy on the re-:\ncent passing of Mrs. Louise\nAgusta Schuster.\nThe Schuster Family\nAR\nFemale et\nPOODLE PUPPIES\ni Tk Balg\ni Village at Cane Bay\nMonday thru Friday\n9 AM. to 6 P.M.\nN,\ni \u2018\ufb02\ufb02l'l\\f }f\ufb02\ufb01*\"\u00ab\nl\"?, \u201c/Q \u2014ale\n7 R\\\nTR\n'NATIONAL LIBR\"\"Y WEEK,\nMarch 1622, 1958~/\nFOR RENT or LEASE\nApprox. 4000 sq. feet space.\nConcrete Bldg. Tile floor,\nrunning water, toilet.\nBox 552 Phone 305\nChristiansted, St. Croix\nPage 3","height":"16473","width":"10914"}}
